snippet.textDisplay: Reminds me of the time I almost got suspended and assault charges because I was defending myself from a bully. Now I don’t recommend physical violence but once they hit you first I will want to see your blood drawn. The fight wasn’t that bad, she pushed me so I punched her and told her to fuck off. My brother and his friends scared her and she went home crying she was so scared that she lied to her mom and she called the police to charge us with assault. Everybody’s story lined up except for hers and all charges were dropped. You think that police report would of been enough for the school to let me off the hook because hey, if the law told me I’m good to go and did nothing wrong shouldn’t the school think that? Well apparently not, I sat in the principals office for half the day waiting for my punishment and he told me he really wanted to suspend me but since I’ve had no other issues then he reluctantly let me go without any punishments. The other girl got suspended tho 😊

snippet.textDisplay:
Lol, I am so much like Greg, just that not quite everybody hated me, and no journal... I don't like those.
Edit: oh I remeber a time, when a bully picked on everybody from class, except me for a time, but when he did, ohh that day...
In the break he threw a couple punches at me, and I thought to myself, hold on, next class is P.E. So in the locker room, as I was getting out and he was coming in at the same time, he bumped intentionally into me, and out of reflex I punched him in the stomach and threw him on the ground. Well, easier than I thought to take care of a bully, he never bothered anyone again.

And next year, a fatass came to our class, 2 years older and 2 heads bigger than everyone else, and he was a bully, he left me alone, although at the time I looked vulnerable being the 3rd shortest boy out of 14.
Once he did, I was with my friend writing some stuff on the chalkboard and he comes behind us to slap both of us at the back of the head, what we BOTH do out of complete reflex, is slap back, and guess what, he gets slapped by both of us, but I slap the right part of his head, and my friend the left, he left both of us the f*ck alone, but he didn't stop doing stuff to everyone else, and 3 years ago he tried flirting with my crush, who was absolutely disgusted by him. So he got back that karma.
